Key Match Events: Simon Msuva scored for Tanzania in the 11th minute
Patson Daka scored a late equalizer for Zambia in the 88th minute
Pre-Game Insights: Tanzania had failed to win in previous finals appearances in 1980 and 2019
Tanzania's coach Adel Amrouche was handed an eight-match suspension
Post-Match Reflections: Zambia salvaged a 1-1 draw to deny Tanzania a first win at the Africa Cup of Nations
Tanzania was not given much chance at the tournament in the Ivory Coast
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match took place at Stade Laurent Pokou
The game was officiated by Djindo Louis Houngnandande
